name: Hobbit Canyon
description:
Introduction

Approach

Descent

The first two rappels are web slings in good pinch points with 50 to 55 foot rappels. There are a few good downclimbs and an 80ish rappel (loose estimate) off a rock chock. Then there is a sketchy downclimb we avoided with a 40 foot rappel we meat anchored. The last person can double strand off a rock horn, but getting the rope back was hard. The last rappel is 150 feet.

Exit
